#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 1 of Year Three is the most safety-critical month of the entire curriculum.
  The Year Three Safety Quiz must be passed and E.3 acknowledged before any
  antimony laboratory work proceeds. Confirm ventilation, PPE, and safe storage
  arrangements for stibnite before the student begins Week 2's practical work.
  The philosophical weeks (1, 3, 4) can proceed in parallel with safety
  confirmation. Do not allow impatience to bypass the safety requirements —
  antimony is a genuine hazard and the curriculum treats it as such.

  The DES-2 inner work shift is significant. Some students will find the
  analytical depth approach more demanding than the DES-1 mapping; others will
  find it clarifying. Either response is appropriate. The key is sustained
  engagement with the deeper archetypal content rather than the surface of
  the imagery.
]

